Certainly, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "nisko" in different forms and positions:

1. *Nisko* se sagao da pokupi novčić koji je ispao. (He bent down *low* to pick up the coin that fell.)
2. Ne volim da sedim *nisko*, jer mi onda boli leđa. (I don't like to sit *low* because it hurts my back.)
3. Oni su se sklonili *nisko* da ne bi bili primećeni. (They hid *low* so they wouldn't be noticed.)
4. Mlada biljka ne sme da bude izložena *niskim* temperaturama. (A young plant must not be exposed to *low* temperatures.)
5. *Niska* cena ne znači uvek da je nešto loše. (A *low* price doesn't always mean something is bad.)
6. Njegova popularnost je *niska* zbog kontroverznih izjava koje je dao. (His popularity is *low* because of controversial statements he made.)

I hope these sentences help illustrate the different ways in which the word "nisko" can be used in Serbian!